I have been getting deliveries, and have also been with family to dine in! Incredible service and wonderful pizza and food! My children were given pages to color, and crayons. They were beyond friendly and attentive to anything we needed!
I recently got a delivery order, and it was multiple orders of the same thing just different condiments. They were prompt, and very kind with everything. After I got my delivery I noticed one of the orders had ketchup which that person does not like ketchup at all. They were so kind when I called to let them know. They also directly delivered the correct order with no charge. If you are looking for some good food and amazing kindness then this is the place for you!

detailedReviews.author: Jerry Meyers
detailedReviews.text:
I stopped in while driving by and thought I would give them a try.  My MO is to order a new place's signature pie, the Pizzazz, on the first visit. I got the thin crust and no sweet peppers.  The deal of the day was a free medium cheese pizza with a large pizza so I got that too.

The sauce was good and just the right amount.  I would get some on the side for dipping the crusts next time.  I think it's the sausage that has a lot of fennel so be careful if you don't like it.  Good mix and amount of toppings but a little light on cheese.

The crust was ok if a little boring.  It was right on the edge of being overworked and tough.  I would like to see it allowed to raise a little longer.  I like a crispier crust but this was ok.

Now I have to order again to check out more of the menu .

detailedReviews.author: Amy Grein
detailedReviews.text:
Fast service. Decent for delivery food. Have had the the pizza a couple times and wings so far. The old bay wings are really good.  We put the pizza in the oven after picking it up to crisp it up a bit.  I was skeptical about this place bc it stayed closed for so long but it's safe to say now that it is the best delivery option in Pittsville.  Any other pizza joint in town is a huge disappointment.  If you are feeling lazy and want delivery in Pittsville, this is the place to order from.

Edit: I would like to add that their chicken breast sandwich is my favorite item to order.  They use real chicken, and it is a large sandwich. My husband orders their cheese burger and he loves it too.  We tried the white pizza and it is amazing.

I am pleasantly surprised at how good the quality of food is.  Also it is very clean in the dining area if you decide to sit down to eat. Highly recommend!

detailedReviews.author: Medic 6934
detailedReviews.text:
I just got their pizza special of 2 large cheese only and let me tell y'all that this place is not light on their toppings! The crust is nice and crisp, a little chewy but in a good way. PERFECT Sauce to cheese ratio. Pizza wasn't so greasy that it instantly drips when folded and bleeds through the box. Price was awesome. For under 25 bucks I have dinner ( and lunch tomorrow) for 4 people. Staff was nice and helpful. To anyone wondering, THIS PLACE IS NOT THE SAME OWNER AS 4 YEARS AGO!!!! That guy was very shady and always tried to slip extra charges in hoping you didn't notice. I guess locals caught on very quick and that's why he opened and closed within 2 years or so.

Back to the NEW Pizza Pizzazz!!!!
I will be ordering again do to the Lightning fast service, very reasonable price and taste of the food. I live very close and they had the order ready as soon as I got there. This place is going to do great with locals and visitors alike I know it.

Thanks again Guy's and Gal's at Pizza Pizzazz you're Awesome! üòé
